{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-js","path":"/world-flag/","result":{"data":{"prismicProject":{"uid":"world-flag","id":"f78bed26-48ae-51a4-879f-04bd2d72cfb6","data":{"project_title":{"html":"<p>World Flag</p>","text":"World Flag"},"client":{"html":"<p>Self-Initiated</p>","text":"Self-Initiated"},"location":{"html":"<p>World, UN</p>","text":"World, UN"},"team":{"html":"<p>Theo Ford</p>","text":"Theo Ford"},"year":{"html":"<p>2015</p>","text":"2015"},"categories":[{"category":{"slug":"identity","id":"ZMfWyhAAACEAPsyd"}}],"body1":[{"id":"text$ecf8cad1-413c-46ce-ac48-cc2b1d92d63c","slice_type":"text","primary":{"text":{"html":"<p>A design for a World Flag to demonstrate solidarity regardless of statehood, religion or creed. Design features include: 23.5 degrees axial tilt of the earth, 71% water to land ratio, and square format for social media. <br /></p><p>This was created in response to the Paris terrorist attacks in 2015, Facebook created a feature allowing users to overlay their profile image with the French Flag. Whilst I appreciated this sentiment, it felt like selective empathy. This was my response: designed for the digital realm and accompanied by a plugin enabling the user to overlay it on their profile image – to show solidarity with all. </p>","text":"A design for a World Flag to demonstrate solidarity regardless of statehood, religion or creed. Design features include: 23.5 degrees axial tilt of the earth, 71% water to land ratio, and square format for social media. \n This was created in response to the Paris terrorist attacks in 2015, Facebook created a feature allowing users to overlay their profile image with the French Flag. Whilst I appreciated this sentiment, it felt like selective empathy. This was my response: designed for the digital realm and accompanied by a plugin enabling the user to overlay it on their profile image – to show solidarity with all. "}}},{"id":"image$79200f86-938a-4ca1-9ba5-ba407825d860","slice_type":"im